Subscribe! https://www.youtube.com/user/seekernetwork?sub_confirmation=1

Meet Connor Macleod, a 13-year-old who is changing paper money to be more inclusive to those who are visually impaired. It is because of Connor’s efforts, that the next generation of Australian banknotes will include tactile features.

